      "message": "Stream-of-consciousness:\n\nI\u0027m initially tempted to keep it like the other SkImage::makeXXX() things, because we have so many, and they\u0027re (theoretically) more discoverable. Except: They have grown out of control, and the pattern only works for a certain subset of operations (exactly one SkImage input, plus some other data). The external factory gets around that limitation, but (maybe) hurts API discoverability.\n\nAnd then I realize that we already have a third pattern that sort-of addresses both of these, which is static factories on SkImage. Would be consider something like:\n\nclass SkImage {\n  static sk_sp\u003cSkImage\u003e MakeWithMipmaps(sk_sp\u003cSkImage\u003e base, SkMipmapBuilder\u0026 mipmaps);\n}\n\n???",
